### Steps to reproduce



In the following example I'm calling a script block on a remote server. The scriptblock receives an `$Inventory` parameter, which is a nested C#  object (depth > 1). It seems that the parameter is only serialized with `depth=1`. Based on `$Inventory | Export-Clixml "$env:TEMP\f2.txt"` I can see that the CLI-XML doesn't contain nested information.

```
var wsManInfo = new WSManConnectionInfo();
var runSpace = RunspaceFactory.CreateRunspace(wsManInfo);
runSpace.Open();
var powerShell = PowerShell.Create();
powerShell.Runspace = runSpace;
powerShell.AddScript(@"
Param($Inventory)


$Inventory | Export-Clixml ""$env:TEMP\f2.txt""


$Inventory.SoftwareInventory.Groups[0].Software

").AddParameter("Inventory", variables);
var results = powerShell.Invoke();
```

Would be great to create an option to set the serialization depth of custom objects.

Actually the depth is `1`, based on `PSObject`:

```
  public virtual void GetObjectData(SerializationInfo info, StreamingContext context)
        {
            if (info == null)
            {
                throw PSTraceSource.NewArgumentNullException(nameof(info));
            }

            // We create a wrapper PSObject, so that we can successfully deserialize it
            string serializedContent;
            if (this.ImmediateBaseObjectIsEmpty)
            {
                PSObject serializeTarget = new PSObject(this);
                serializedContent = PSSerializer.Serialize(serializeTarget);
            }
            else
            {
                serializedContent = PSSerializer.Serialize(this);
            }

            info.AddValue("CliXml", serializedContent);
        }
```

Is it possible to set the serialization depth via the API?


### Expected behavior

```console
A custom object shall be serialized in required depth.
```


### Actual behavior

```console
A custom object is serialized with depth=1.
```


